'''Richardson's Tavern''' is a historic [[Erie Canal]] [[inn]] and [[tavern]] located in the hamlet of [[Bushnell's Basin]] in [[Perinton, New York|Perinton]], [[Monroe County, New York]]. It dates to about 1818 when it was a stop on the stage coach route along the Irondequoit Valley and Irondequoit Creek, between [[Rochester, New York|Rochester]] and [[Canandaigua, New York|Canandaigua]].<ref name=D&C_May2012>{{cite news|last=Morrell|first=Alan|title=Eatery enjoys revival|url=http://www.democratandchronicle.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=2012305270024|accessdate=May 28, 2012|newspaper=[[Democrat and Chronicle]]|date=May 28, 2012|agency=[[Gannett Company]]|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/67zGMqZQh|archivedate=May 28, 2012|location=[[Rochester, New York]]|page=6K}}</ref>   Several expansions occurred during the 19th century.  The tavern operated as a hotel until 1917 when it was converted to four apartments. In 1978, after having been abandoned since 1972, it was converted for use as a restaurant, '''Richardson's Canal House'''.<ref name="nrhpinv_ny">{{cite web|url=http://www.oprhp.state.ny.us/hpimaging/hp_view.asp?GroupView=4086|title=National Register of Historic Places Registration: Richardson's Tavern|date=January 1980|accessdate=2009-10-20 |author=Robert Englert|publisher=[[New York State Office of Parks, Recreation and Historic Preservation]]}} ''See also:'' {{cite web|url=http://www.oprhp.state.ny.us/hpimaging/hp_view.asp?GroupView=4087|title=Accompanying nine photos}}</ref>   The restaurant opened on Valentine's Day 1979.<ref name=D&C_May2012 />  It has become one of the most noted restaurants in the county.<ref name=D&C_May2012 />

It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1980.<ref name="nris"/>

